{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XcGGoYAUmUc1W4zxKLM3Tj","type":"tool_result","content":"   214→\n   215→Based on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n   216→\n   217→#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n   218→\n   219→Handles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n   220→\n   221→- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n   222→- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n   223→  bullet/rule\n   224→- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n   225→  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n   226→- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n   227→  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n   228→  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n   229→- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n   230→\n   231→#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n   232→\n   233→Handles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n   234→\n   235→- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n   236→- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n   237→  prompt file for agent steps\n   238→- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n   239→  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n   240→- Output: the file path and content\n   241→\n   242→#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n   243→\n   244→Handles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\n   245→them to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n   246→\n   247→**Add Step Definition:**\n   248→```json\n   249→{\n   250→  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n   251→  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n   252→  \"type\": \"script\",\n   253→  \"config\": {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dfc0695-6634-43c9-8fed-44daebf0ccee","uuid":"5dce3823-2629-4e1a-9610-768d8c41e868","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"\nBased on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n\n#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n\nHandles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n\n- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n  bullet/rule\n- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n\n#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n\nHandles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n\n- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n  prompt file for agent steps\n- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n- Output: the file path and content\n\n#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n\nHandles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\nthem to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n\n**Add Step Definition:**\n```json\n{\n  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n  \"type\": \"script\",\n  \"config\": {","numLines":40,"startLine":214,"totalLines":449}}}
